<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 02-47-04R - Relocation of the Entrance Door Control Switch / Installation of Pivot Plate Thrust Bearings
        Slide Handle Retaining Screw Installation
    </stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi024704R" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>02-47-04R</tsinumber>
        <replace>
            <tsinumber>02-47-04</tsinumber>
        </replace>
        <tsidate>March, 2002</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>BUS BODY</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Relocation of the Entrance Door Control Switch / Installation of Pivot Plate Thrust Bearings Slide
                Handle Retaining Screw Installation
            </subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>IC Bus</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The procedures included are designed to improve the overall function and reliability of the Linear
                    Door Control. Relocating the entrance door control switch from its original location at the end of
                    the handle track to the side of the bracket eliminates failures in the switch due to the handle
                    contact with the switch. The addition of the thrust bearings on the pivot plate allows the plate to
                    be torqued to ensure reliable, consistent movement. The addition of Loctite to the slide handle
                    screw threads eliminates the need to inspect or re-tighten the slide handle installation.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
