        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Area Preparation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove right hand dash cover by removing the snap covers and screws (9 total) securing
                    it to the dash.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0247041" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0247041.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Dash Cover Removal</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove door control rod from the pivot plate and rotate toward front of unit for
                    additional workspace.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove lower dash plate.</para>
                <figure id="f0247042" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0247042.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                             scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2. Lower Dash Panel Removal</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Switch Bracket Replacement</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the new bracket in proper location and mark hole (2) locations per drawings.
                    (Field fix kit, Forward Folding - 452354001, and Outward Opening - 452354002 includes necessary
                    reference information and parts.)
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drill (2) 0.213-in. holes and install bracket with screws and lock nuts hand tight only.
                    To gain additional room for the drilling process, the defrost duct can be loosened from the right
                    hand corner and center position and raised toward roof.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0247043" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0247043.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Switch Bracket Installation</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach switch to the new bracket using the existing hardware.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0247044" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0247044.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Switch Installation</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If no other modifications are to be performed, proceed to door Adjustment Procedures at
                    the end of this document.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="5">
            <title>Pivot Plate Thrust Bearing Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen setscrew on rear side of main pivot bolt (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0247045">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0247045" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0247045.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Loosen Setscrew on Main Pivot Bolt</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove main pivot plate bolt and pivot plate slide bolt and washers (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0247046">Figure 6</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0247046" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0247046.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Remove Main and Slide Pivot Plate Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift pivot plate up and rotate toward front of unit.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove fiber washers from main pivot plate location and discard. Remove the nylon slip
                    pad from the top of the slide handle assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0247047">Figure 7</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0247047" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0247047.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Remove Fiber Washer and Nylon Slide Pad</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect pivot plate and pivot boss areas to ensure they are clean. Place a thrust
                    bearing race, bearing and race on the main pivot boss (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0247048">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If the pivot bolt is a shoulder bolt, the top thrust bearing lower race will not be utilized.
                        Install the thrust bearing directly on the pivot plate.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0247048" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0247048.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Place Races and Bearing on Pivot Boss</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place pivot plate on lower thrust bearings and install two races and bearing between the
                    pivot plate and the main pivot bolt head (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0247049">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0247049" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0247049.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 9. Re-install Pivot Plate</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check position of bearings to ensure proper alignment and torque bolt to 80 inch pounds.
                    Retighten main pivot bolt setscrew loosened in step 1.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install pivot plate slide washers and nut. Nut should be tightened to allow plate to
                    slide with very little vertical play.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If no other modifications are to be performed, proceed to door Adjustment Procedure at
                    the end of this document.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Slide Handle Retaining screw installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove one slide handle screw and apply loctite to the screw threads (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f024704a">Figure 10</hotlnk>). Re-install the screw and repeat process on remaining
                    three screws. The two screws at the rear of the slide handle can be accessed through an access hole
                    in the bottom of the mounting plate (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f024704b">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f024704a" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G024704A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Slide Handle Front Screws</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f024704b" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G024704B.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Slide Handle Rear Screw Access Hole</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Adjustment Procedures</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install door control rod and lower dash plate.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Start engine and test operation of door and applicable lights. Adjust switch and door
                    adjustment points as necessary for correct operation.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten switch, switch bracket mounting screws and all door adjustment points.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Further instructions on Linear Door Adjustment can be found in TSI 01-47-01.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install right hand dash cover.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
